    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "In the implementation, the modifier implementation in derived class will have to use the `override` flag.\r\n\r\nThe same example:\r\n\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.19;\r\n\r\ncontract A {\r\n    modifier readyToAct;\r\n    \r\n    function act() readyToAct external {\r\n        \r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract B is A {\r\n    modifier readyToAct override {\r\n        require(true);\r\n        _;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis check already happens in the code, and makes the code clearer, so I'll keep it. What do you think @ekpyron ",
